8.4 Variance Inflation Factors (Multicollinearity)


Code
vif_data = pd.DataFrame({
    "Feature": ["wt", "hp", "cyl"],
    "VIF": [
        variance_inflation_factor(X_exog.values, i+1)
        for i in range(3)
    ]
}).round(2)

vif_data["Flag"] = vif_data["VIF"].apply(
    lambda v: "⚠️ High" if v &gt; 10 else ("🔶 Moderate" if v &gt; 5 else "✅ OK")
)
vif_data



Rule of thumb: VIF &gt; 10 signals severe multicollinearity; VIF &gt; 5 warrants attention.
